Subject: fmha bwd: zero dq_acc workspace for deterministic group/varlen mode

The ck_tile launcher only zeroes the dq_acc workspace when its compile-time
NeedsZeroDqAcc() gate is set. For deterministic group/varlen mode that gate does
not fire for every mask/layout (non-causal padding in particular), so the
split-accumulator slots for padded/masked KV are left uninitialized and the
convert_dq reduction reads stale memory -> non-deterministic dq. Request
zero-init from the caller-provided allocator for that case so the whole
workspace starts zeroed. Batch mode is already covered by the launcher's own
persistent-path zeroing.

diff --git a/csrc/cpp_itfs/mha_bwd.cu b/csrc/cpp_itfs/mha_bwd.cu
--- a/csrc/cpp_itfs/mha_bwd.cu
+++ b/csrc/cpp_itfs/mha_bwd.cu
@@ -163,6 +163,7 @@

     fmha_bwd_launcher launcher(traits);
-    void* workspace_ptr = a.workspace_alloc(launcher.workspace_size, /*zero_init=*/false);
+    const bool zero_ws = a.is_deterministic && a.is_group_mode;
+    void* workspace_ptr = a.workspace_alloc(launcher.workspace_size, /*zero_init=*/zero_ws);

     // Enqueues the workspace prep on the caller's stream: dq_acc zero (if needed)
     // plus an on-device kernel that writes the nsplits[]/offsets[] metadata. Fully
